Abdomen: With light dark-brown tergites, each tergite with spots of diffuse silver pollinosity. Sternite 5 rectangular with sides slightly rounded, with long bristles on the sides and apex, posterior margin of sclerotized area with large invagination rounded in the mid region (
Fig. 43
). Terminalia: cerci longer than surstylus, fused on basal two-thirds, with long bristles on the apex and sides (
Figs. 44, 45
). Surstylus with broader base than the apex, in dorsal view with apical curvature and several scattered fine setae (
Fig. 46
). Parameres trilobed, with preapical lobe on the middle, as thick as one of the apical lobes (
Fig. 47
). Aedeagus with preapical, spine-like unsclerotized projection, apex and ventral middle portion more sclerotized (
Figs. 48, 49
). Epiphallus with apical region curved and rounded and with short branches (
Figs. 48, 49
).

